        "content": "<p>So with issues like <a href=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/4052\" title=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/4052\">#4052</a>, why does this happen? Why is RA blocking Enter keys from following through to the editor?</p>",
        "id": 194664975,
        "sender_full_name": "Dirkjan Ochtman",
        "timestamp": 1587384170
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm experiencing the same thing today with this week's build and have encountered it in the past as well (for example <a href=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/3782\" title=\"https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/3782\">#3782</a>)</p>",
        "id": 194665063,
        "sender_full_name": "Dirkjan Ochtman",
        "timestamp": 1587384227
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>and it is incredibly frustrating</p>",
        "id": 194665089,
        "sender_full_name": "Dirkjan Ochtman",
        "timestamp": 1587384242
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Rust analyzer tries to for example insert <code>///</code> after pressing enter inside a doc comment.</p>",
        "id": 194665549,
        "sender_full_name": "bjorn3",
        "timestamp": 1587384585
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://github.com/rust-analyzer/rust-analyzer/blob/bddf6b5266997dd7e017fcb963e54a86b68afbaa/crates/ra_ide/src/typing/on_enter.rs#L16\" title=\"https://github.com/rust-analyzer/rust-analyzer/blob/bddf6b5266997dd7e017fcb963e54a86b68afbaa/crates/ra_ide/src/typing/on_enter.rs#L16\">https://github.com/rust-analyzer/rust-analyzer/blob/bddf6b5266997dd7e017fcb963e54a86b68afbaa/crates/ra_ide/src/typing/on_enter.rs#L16</a></p>",
        "id": 194665841,
        "sender_full_name": "bjorn3",
        "timestamp": 1587384778
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You should be able to disable the keybinding in <code>Preferences: Open Keyboard Shortcuts</code>. The binding is called <code>rust-analyzer.onEnter</code>. You need to right click to remove it.</p>",
        "id": 194666176,
        "sender_full_name": "bjorn3",
        "timestamp": 1587384996
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>alright then</p>",
